    • Class streamcorpus.ContentItem extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          private void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException
          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException

        • writeObject

          private void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream out)
                  throws java.io.IOException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException

      • Serialized Fields

        • raw

          java.nio.ByteBuffer raw
          original download, raw byte array

        • encoding

          java.lang.String encoding
          guessed from raw and/or headers, e.g. by python-requests.org

        • media_type

          java.lang.String media_type
          Content-type header from fetching the data, or MIME type

        • clean_html

          java.lang.String clean_html
          HTML-formatted version of raw with UTF8 encoding and no broken tags. All HTML-escaped characters are converted to their UTF8 equivalents. < > & are escaped.

        • clean_visible

          java.lang.String clean_visible
          All tags stripped from clean_html and replaced with whitespace, so they have the same byte offsets. The only escaped characters are < > &, so that this can be treated as Character Data in XML: http://www.w3.org/TR/xml/#syntax Again: must be UTF8

        • logs

          java.util.List<E> logs
          Logs generated from processing pipeline, for forensics

        • taggings

          java.util.Map<K,V> taggings
          A set of auto-generated taggings, such as a One-Word-Per-Line (OWLP) tokenization and sentence chunking with part-of-speech, lemmatization, and NER classification. The string name should be the same as the tagger_id and also corresponds to the key in sentences or sentence_blobs, which get generated by transforming a Tagging.raw_tagging into Sentence and Token instances Taggings are generated from 'clean_visible' so offsets (byte, char, line) refer to clean_visible and clean_html -- not raw.

        • labels

          java.util.Map<K,V> labels
          sets of annotations

        • sentences

          java.util.Map<K,V> sentences
          parsed Sentence objects generated by an NLP pipeline identified by the string name, which is a tagger_id that connects this Sentences instance to the Tagging struct from which it came

        • sentence_blobs

          java.util.Map<K,V> sentence_blobs
          same as 'sentences' except the array of Sentence instances are serialized into a binary string that can be read by the Thrift's binary protocol. This allows lazy deserialization via an iterator -- one sentence at a time. This might be totally unnecessary, because at least some of the Thrift language implementations have lazy object construction, e.g. --gen py:dynamic,slots

        • language

          Language language
          indication of which natural language is used in the text

        • optionals

          ContentItem._Fields[] optionals

                  throws java.io.IOException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException

      • Serialized Fields

        • type

          OffsetType type
          see comments on OffsetType
          See Also:
          OffsetType

        • first

          long first
          actual offset, which could be measured in bytes, chars, or lines. The data element identified by 'first' is included, and that identified by first+length is also included. In set notation, [first:first+length] or equivalently [first:first+length+1) While thrift treats these as signed integers, negative values are meaningless in this context, i.e. we do not end wrap.

        • length

          int length

        • xpath

          java.lang.String xpath
          if xpath is not empty, then annotation applies to an offset within data that starts with an XPATH query into XHTML or XML

        • content_form

          java.lang.String content_form
          name of the data element inside a ContentItem to which this label applies, e.g. 'raw' 'clean_html' or 'clean_visible'. Defaults to clean_visible, which is the most common case.

        • value

          java.nio.ByteBuffer value
          bytes specified by this offset extracted from the original; just to assist in debugging

          byte __isset_bitfield

          Offset._Fields[] optionals

        • writeObject

          private void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream out)
                  throws java.io.IOException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException

      • Serialized Fields

        • annotator

          Annotator annotator
          identifies the source of this Rating

        • target

          Target target
          identifies the information need assessed by annotator

        • relevance

          short relevance
          numerical score assigned by annotator to "judge" or "rate" the utility of this StreamItem to addressing the target information need. The range and interpretation of relevance numbers depends on the annotator. relevance can represent a rank ordering or an enumeration such as -1=Garbage, 0=Neutral, 1=Useful, 2=Vital

        • contains_mention

          boolean contains_mention
          true|false indication of whether the document mentions the target entity. This is only partially correlated with relevance. For example, a document might mention the entity only in chrome text on the side such that it is a Garbage-rated text for that entity.

        • comments

          java.lang.String comments
          Save notes from Annotator about this Rating

        • mentions

          java.util.List<E> mentions
          Record strings that are "mentions" of the target in this text

        • __isset_bitfield

          byte __isset_bitfield

        • optionals

          Rating._Fields[] optionals

    • Class streamcorpus.StreamItem extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          private void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException
          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException

        • writeObject

          private void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream out)
                  throws java.io.IOException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException

      • Serialized Fields

        • version

          Versions version
          must provide a version number here
          See Also:
          Versions

        • doc_id

          java.lang.String doc_id
          md5 hash of the abs_url

        • abs_url

          java.nio.ByteBuffer abs_url
          normalized form of the original_url, should be a valid URL

        • schost

          java.lang.String schost
          scheme://hostname parsed from abs_url

        • original_url

          java.nio.ByteBuffer original_url
          string obtain from some source. Only present if not a valid URL, in which case abs_url was derived from original_url

        • source

          java.lang.String source
          string uniquely identifying this data set, should start with a year string, such as 'news' or 'social'

        • body

          ContentItem body
          primary content

        • source_metadata

          java.util.Map<K,V> source_metadata
          see above for explanation of the values that can appear in this dictionary of metadata info from the source. The string keys in this map should be short, descriptive, and free of whitespace.

        • stream_id

          java.lang.String stream_id
          stream_id is actual unique identifier for a StreamItem. The format is: stream_id = '%d-%s' % (int(stream_time.epoch_ticks), doc_id)

        • stream_time

          StreamTime stream_time
          earliest time that this content was known to exist. Usually, body.raw was also saved at the time of that first observation.

        • other_content

          java.util.Map<K,V> other_content
          such as title, anchor, extracted, etc. When present, 'anchor', is a single anchor text of a URL pointing to this doc. Note that this does not have metadata like the URL of the page that contained this anchor. Such general link graph data may eventually motivate an extension to this thrift interface.

        • ratings

          java.util.Map<K,V> ratings
          doc-level judgments relating entire StreamItem to a Target

        • optionals

          StreamItem._Fields[] optionals

    • Class streamcorpus.Token extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          private void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException
          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException

        • writeObject

          private void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream out)
                  throws java.io.IOException
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException

      • Serialized Fields

        • token_num

          int token_num
          zero-based index into the stream of tokens from a document

        • token

          java.lang.String token
          actual token string, must always be a UTF8 encoded string, not a unicode string, because thrift stores them as 8-bit.

        • offsets

          java.util.Map<K,V> offsets
          offsets into the original data (see Offset.content_form)

        • sentence_pos

          int sentence_pos
          zero-based index into the sentence, which is used for dependency parsed data

        • lemma

          java.lang.String lemma
          lemmatization of the token, again must be UTF8

        • pos

          java.lang.String pos
          part of speech labels defined by Penn TreeBank: http://www.ling.upenn.edu/courses/Fall_2003/ling001/penn_treebank_pos.html Should probably convert this to an enum, analogous to EntityType

        • entity_type

          EntityType entity_type
          entity type from named entity recognizer (classifier)
          See Also:
          EntityType

        • mention_id

          short mention_id
          Identifier for a multi-token mention starts at zero for each sentence, because we assume mentions cannot cross sentence boundaries. Really only needed when the entity_type and equiv_id do not change between tokens that are part of separate mentions, e.g. "The senator is known to his friends as David, Davy, Zeus, and Mr. Elephant."

        • equiv_id

          int equiv_id
          Within-doc coref chain ID. That is, identifier of equivalence class of co-referent tokens. Default is -1, meaning None.

        • parent_id

          int parent_id
          parent sentence_pos in dependency parse. Default is -1, ie None

        • dependency_path

          java.lang.String dependency_path
          grammatical relation label on path to parent in dependency parse, defined by whatever tagger was used -- should pick a canonical definition here and convert it to an enum.

        • labels

          java.util.Map<K,V> labels
          Labels attached to this token, defaults to an empty map

        • __isset_bitfield

          byte __isset_bitfield

        • optionals

          Token._Fields[] optionals
